I LOST MY MOTHER THIS 4TH OF JULY DUE TO A SUDDEN HEART ATTACK.  SHE WAS A VERY LOVING AND GIVING PERSON WHO BELIVED THAT ONE HAND SHOULD ALWAYS BE OPEN IN THE ACT OF GIVEIING. INTO HER OTHER HAND SHE BELIVED MORE WOULD BE GIVEN.  I THINK HER POINT WAS IF WE HOLD ON TIGHT TO WHAT WE HAVE BEEN BLESSED WITH, THE BLESSING WILL STOP.
SOMETIMES THINGS ARE JUST MEANT TO PASS THROUGH US TO OTHERS.
 IN THE LAST YEARS OF HER LIFE SHE GAVE HER MONEY TO "TV CHURCHS" AS SHE WAS HOUSE BOUND DUE TO MY STEP- FATHER'S ILLNESS, AND CARING FOR HIM 24/7. 

SHE AND I HAD TALKED ABOUT KIVA AND THE WORK IT WAS DOING "PERSON TO PERSON" AND I AM SENDING HER 10% OUT INTO THE WORLD IN HER HONOR.

I MISS HER VERY MUCH AND HOPE THAT THESE LOANS WILL HELP OTHERS MAKE THEIR WAY INTO A BETTER LIFE, TAKE CARE, ROBYN
